{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NwDgzEzzfW5xn1Fyk2kmHG","type":"tool_result","content":"- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n--\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n\nFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DRJpD1eM96SarjwC2tMEGw","session_id":"8b59bc36-4d9a-4087-87ff-725aff05648e","uuid":"c0dca72d-e3e5-490d-814d-89245ff5c49e"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a0ed40e386532bf08","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DRJpD1eM96SarjwC2tMEGw","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore cloche logs implementation","usage":{"total_tokens":72918,"tool_uses":36,"duration_ms":105055},"uuid":"9f3e68d4-1612-4e50-840a-791261ecbbc3","session_id":"8b59bc36-4d9a-4087-87ff-725aff05648e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DRJpD1eM96SarjwC2tMEGw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary of all my findings:\n\n## Summary: Cloche Logs Implementation Architecture\n\n### 1. CLI Command Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 263-410)\n\nThe `cloche logs` command implementation:\n- **Command signature:** `cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]`\n- **Main function:** `cmdLogs()` (line 263)\n- **Follow implementation:** `cmdLogsFollow()` (line 349)\n\nKey implementation details:\n- Parses arguments for `--step`, `--type`, and `--follow` flags\n- Without `--follow`: Uses gRPC `StreamLogs` RPC (line 296)\n- With `--follow`: Switches to HTTP SSE endpoint via `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var (line 351)\n- Context-less for log streaming: `context.Background()` used to allow large output without timeouts\n\n### 2. gRPC Service Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 1-119)\n\nService definition:\n- RPC: `rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry);` (line 10)\n- Request message `StreamLogsRequest` (lines 58-62):\n  - `string run_id`\n  - `string step_name` (optional filter)\n  - `string log_type` (optional filter)\n- Response message `LogEntry` (lines 64-70):\n  - `string type` (e.g., \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"full_log\", \"log\")\n  - `string step_name`\n  - `string result`\n  - `string message`\n  - `string timestamp`\n\n### 3. gRPC Server Implementation\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\nMain streaming function `StreamLogs()` (lines 466-565):\n- Verifies run exists\n- Routes based on filters:\n  - If `step_name` or `log_type` set → calls `streamFilteredLogs()`\n  - For active runs (pending/running) with broadcaster → calls `streamLiveLogs()`\n  - For completed runs → streams from full.log (unified log file)\n  - Falls back to capture-based streaming from per-step log files\n\nFiltered logs function `streamFilteredLogs()` (lines 569-635):\n- Uses log index (ports.LogStore) when available\n- Falls back to file path conventions (e.g., `llm-<step>.log`)\n- Sends content as SSE or gRPC log entries\n\nLive logs function `streamLiveLogs()` (lines 640-673):\n- Subscribes to the log broadcaster\n- Streams real-time LogLine entries from active runs\n- Sends \"run_completed\" event when run finishes\n- Closes on client disconnect\n\n### 4. Log Streaming Infrastructure\n\n#### Broadcaster (Publisher-Subscriber)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` (lines 1-141)\n\n- Thread-safe fan-out to multiple subscribers\n- Per-run channels with 256-buffer capacity\n- Non-blocking publish (drops slow subscribers)\n- Marks runs as finished to prevent late subscribes from getting stale channels\n- Used during container execution to stream LLM output in real time\n\nLogLine structure (lines 8-13):\n```go\ntype LogLine struct {\n    Timestamp string\n    Type      string   // \"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    Content   string   \n    StepName  string\n}\n```\n\n#### Log Writer\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` (lines 1-68)\n\n- Writes timestamped, type-prefixed entries to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n- Thread-safe concurrent writes\n- Format: `[timestamp] [type] message`\n\n#### Log Parsing\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` (lines 1-233)\n\n- `ParseClaudeLine()`: Parses individual Claude Code stream-json lines (assistant, result, content_block_delta, content_block_start events)\n- `ParseClaudeStream()`: Batch processing of raw Claude output\n- Tool call extraction: Formats tool invocations with parameters\n- Skips protocol-only events (system, user, etc.)\n\n### 5. HTTP SSE Streaming (Follow Mode)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nHandler `handleAPIStream()` (lines 818-884):\n- Endpoint: `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`\n- Sets SSE headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`\n- For completed runs: Streams archived full.log file\n- For active runs: Subscribes to broadcaster and streams live\n\nHelper `streamFullLog()` (lines 889-912):\n- Reads full.log line by line\n- Parses timestamp and type\n- Extracts human-readable text from LLM JSON\n- Sends as SSE data events\n\nParsing helpers:\n- `parseFullLogLine()` (lines 930-945): Regex parsing of `[timestamp] [type] content` format\n- `parseLLMLogLine()` (lines 914-928): Extracts human text from Claude stream JSON\n\n### 6. Environment Variables\n\n- `CLOCHE_ADDR`: gRPC daemon address (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n- `CLOCHE_HTTP`: HTTP web dashboard address (no default; SSE requires this to be set)\n- Both used by CLI client in `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n### 7. Log Files and Storage\n\nDirectory structure (`.cloche/<run-id>/output/`):\n- `full.log`: Unified timestamped log of all events\n- `<step-name>.log`: Per-step output\n- `llm-<step-name>.log`: LLM-type logs for specific steps\n- `container.log`: Full container stdout/stderr before extraction\n- `script.log`, etc.: Type-specific logs\n\n### 8. Log Index (Optional)\n**Ports:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (lines 26-41)\n\n`LogStore` interface for indexed lookups:\n- `SaveLogFile()`: Index extracted log files\n- `GetLogFiles()`: All logs for a run\n- `GetLogFilesByStep()`: Logs for specific step\n- `GetLogFileByType()`: Logs by type (script, llm, full)\n\n### 9. Tracking and Publishing During Execution\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 188-384)\n\nIn `trackRun()` during container execution:\n- Parses JSON-line status messages from agent output\n- For `MsgLog`: Publishes to broadcaster with type \"llm\"\n- For `MsgStepStarted`/`MsgStepCompleted`: Publishes status entries\n- Calls `logBroadcast.Finish(runID)` when run completes\n- Extracts output files from container before removal\n\n### 10. Integration in Daemon\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\nInitialization (lines 61-91):\n- Creates broadcaster: `logstream.NewBroadcaster()`\n- Attaches to gRPC server: `srv.SetLogBroadcaster(broadcaster)`\n- Creates web handler with broadcaster option: `web.WithLogBroadcaster(broadcaster)`\n- Serves on HTTP address if `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var set\n\n### 11. Testing\n**Files:** \n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`: `TestServer_StreamLogs()` - Tests gRPC log streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`: SSE streaming tests\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster_test.go`: Broadcaster tests\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse_test.go`: Parsing tests\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Dual-mode streaming**: gRPC for real-time, HTTP/SSE for follow mode\n2. **Event-driven architecture**: Broadcaster pattern for live logs\n3. **Unified log format**: All log types written to single full.log with consistent format\n4. **Graceful fallback**: Full.log takes precedence; falls back to per-step files\n5. **Claude stream parsing**: Intelligent extraction of human-readable text from protocol JSON\n6. **Non-blocking publish**: Slow subscribers are dropped to prevent backpressure\n\n---\n\n**File Paths (Absolute):**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0ed40e386532bf08 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75084\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 105058</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b59bc36-4d9a-4087-87ff-725aff05648e","uuid":"a90f1e0e-9595-45ff-b88f-a92bb15cbb0a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand how `cloche logs` is currently implemented. I need to find:\n\n1. The CLI command definition for `cloche logs` (likely in cmd/cloche/)\n2. Any existing follow/streaming logic for logs\n3. The gRPC service definitions related to logs\n4. The ports/adapters for log streaming\n5. Any existing tests for the logs command\n6. How CLOCHE_HTTP and --follow currently work\n\nBe very thorough - search for \"logs\", \"follow\", \"stream\", \"LogStream\", \"tail\" across the codebase. Look at proto files, gRPC service definitions, and the daemon implementation.","agentId":"a0ed40e386532bf08","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary of all my findings:\n\n## Summary: Cloche Logs Implementation Architecture\n\n### 1. CLI Command Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 263-410)\n\nThe `cloche logs` command implementation:\n- **Command signature:** `cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]`\n- **Main function:** `cmdLogs()` (line 263)\n- **Follow implementation:** `cmdLogsFollow()` (line 349)\n\nKey implementation details:\n- Parses arguments for `--step`, `--type`, and `--follow` flags\n- Without `--follow`: Uses gRPC `StreamLogs` RPC (line 296)\n- With `--follow`: Switches to HTTP SSE endpoint via `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var (line 351)\n- Context-less for log streaming: `context.Background()` used to allow large output without timeouts\n\n### 2. gRPC Service Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 1-119)\n\nService definition:\n- RPC: `rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry);` (line 10)\n- Request message `StreamLogsRequest` (lines 58-62):\n  - `string run_id`\n  - `string step_name` (optional filter)\n  - `string log_type` (optional filter)\n- Response message `LogEntry` (lines 64-70):\n  - `string type` (e.g., \"step_started\", \"step_completed\", \"run_completed\", \"full_log\", \"log\")\n  - `string step_name`\n  - `string result`\n  - `string message`\n  - `string timestamp`\n\n### 3. gRPC Server Implementation\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\nMain streaming function `StreamLogs()` (lines 466-565):\n- Verifies run exists\n- Routes based on filters:\n  - If `step_name` or `log_type` set → calls `streamFilteredLogs()`\n  - For active runs (pending/running) with broadcaster → calls `streamLiveLogs()`\n  - For completed runs → streams from full.log (unified log file)\n  - Falls back to capture-based streaming from per-step log files\n\nFiltered logs function `streamFilteredLogs()` (lines 569-635):\n- Uses log index (ports.LogStore) when available\n- Falls back to file path conventions (e.g., `llm-<step>.log`)\n- Sends content as SSE or gRPC log entries\n\nLive logs function `streamLiveLogs()` (lines 640-673):\n- Subscribes to the log broadcaster\n- Streams real-time LogLine entries from active runs\n- Sends \"run_completed\" event when run finishes\n- Closes on client disconnect\n\n### 4. Log Streaming Infrastructure\n\n#### Broadcaster (Publisher-Subscriber)\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` (lines 1-141)\n\n- Thread-safe fan-out to multiple subscribers\n- Per-run channels with 256-buffer capacity\n- Non-blocking publish (drops slow subscribers)\n- Marks runs as finished to prevent late subscribes from getting stale channels\n- Used during container execution to stream LLM output in real time\n\nLogLine structure (lines 8-13):\n```go\ntype LogLine struct {\n    Timestamp string\n    Type      string   // \"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    Content   string   \n    StepName  string\n}\n```\n\n#### Log Writer\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` (lines 1-68)\n\n- Writes timestamped, type-prefixed entries to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n- Thread-safe concurrent writes\n- Format: `[timestamp] [type] message`\n\n#### Log Parsing\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` (lines 1-233)\n\n- `ParseClaudeLine()`: Parses individual Claude Code stream-json lines (assistant, result, content_block_delta, content_block_start events)\n- `ParseClaudeStream()`: Batch processing of raw Claude output\n- Tool call extraction: Formats tool invocations with parameters\n- Skips protocol-only events (system, user, etc.)\n\n### 5. HTTP SSE Streaming (Follow Mode)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nHandler `handleAPIStream()` (lines 818-884):\n- Endpoint: `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`\n- Sets SSE headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`\n- For completed runs: Streams archived full.log file\n- For active runs: Subscribes to broadcaster and streams live\n\nHelper `streamFullLog()` (lines 889-912):\n- Reads full.log line by line\n- Parses timestamp and type\n- Extracts human-readable text from LLM JSON\n- Sends as SSE data events\n\nParsing helpers:\n- `parseFullLogLine()` (lines 930-945): Regex parsing of `[timestamp] [type] content` format\n- `parseLLMLogLine()` (lines 914-928): Extracts human text from Claude stream JSON\n\n### 6. Environment Variables\n\n- `CLOCHE_ADDR`: gRPC daemon address (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n- `CLOCHE_HTTP`: HTTP web dashboard address (no default; SSE requires this to be set)\n- Both used by CLI client in `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n### 7. Log Files and Storage\n\nDirectory structure (`.cloche/<run-id>/output/`):\n- `full.log`: Unified timestamped log of all events\n- `<step-name>.log`: Per-step output\n- `llm-<step-name>.log`: LLM-type logs for specific steps\n- `container.log`: Full container stdout/stderr before extraction\n- `script.log`, etc.: Type-specific logs\n\n### 8. Log Index (Optional)\n**Ports:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (lines 26-41)\n\n`LogStore` interface for indexed lookups:\n- `SaveLogFile()`: Index extracted log files\n- `GetLogFiles()`: All logs for a run\n- `GetLogFilesByStep()`: Logs for specific step\n- `GetLogFileByType()`: Logs by type (script, llm, full)\n\n### 9. Tracking and Publishing During Execution\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 188-384)\n\nIn `trackRun()` during container execution:\n- Parses JSON-line status messages from agent output\n- For `MsgLog`: Publishes to broadcaster with type \"llm\"\n- For `MsgStepStarted`/`MsgStepCompleted`: Publishes status entries\n- Calls `logBroadcast.Finish(runID)` when run completes\n- Extracts output files from container before removal\n\n### 10. Integration in Daemon\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\nInitialization (lines 61-91):\n- Creates broadcaster: `logstream.NewBroadcaster()`\n- Attaches to gRPC server: `srv.SetLogBroadcaster(broadcaster)`\n- Creates web handler with broadcaster option: `web.WithLogBroadcaster(broadcaster)`\n- Serves on HTTP address if `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var set\n\n### 11. Testing\n**Files:** \n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`: `TestServer_StreamLogs()` - Tests gRPC log streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`: SSE streaming tests\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster_test.go`: Broadcaster tests\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse_test.go`: Parsing tests\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Dual-mode streaming**: gRPC for real-time, HTTP/SSE for follow mode\n2. **Event-driven architecture**: Broadcaster pattern for live logs\n3. **Unified log format**: All log types written to single full.log with consistent format\n4. **Graceful fallback**: Full.log takes precedence; falls back to per-step files\n5. **Claude stream parsing**: Intelligent extraction of human-readable text from protocol JSON\n6. **Non-blocking publish**: Slow subscribers are dropped to prevent backpressure\n\n---\n\n**File Paths (Absolute):**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":105058,"totalTokens":75084,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":762,"cache_read_input_tokens":72068,"output_tokens":2251,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":762},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
