{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JyrzsiKrQgSwoCKf27mxBb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Proto** (`api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`): Added `bool follow = 4` field to `StreamLogsRequest` with documentation.\n\n**gRPC Server** (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`):\n- Added `followFromContext()` helper that reads `x-cloche-follow` from gRPC metadata\n- Added `streamFollowLogs()` method that sends existing `full.log` content first, then subscribes to the broadcaster for live tailing (like `tail -f`)\n- Changed `StreamLogs` behavior: without `-f`, active runs now return a snapshot of existing logs and exit; with `-f`, they stream existing logs then continue tailing live output\n\n**CLI** (`cmd/cloche/main.go`):\n- When `-f` is passed, attaches `x-cloche-follow: true` gRPC metadata to the context\n- Removed the `cmdLogsFollow()` function that required HTTP SSE via `CLOCHE_HTTP`\n- All log streaming now goes through a single gRPC `StreamLogs` path\n\n**Tests** (`internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`):\n- Updated existing `TestServer_StreamLogs_LiveStreaming` and `TestServer_StreamLogs_LiveStreamingClientDisconnect` to use follow metadata\n- Added `TestServer_StreamLogs_NoFollowActiveRun` — verifies snapshot behavior without `-f`\n- Added `TestServer_StreamLogs_FollowWithExistingLogs` — verifies existing logs are sent before live tailing\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":293,"cache_read_input_tokens":67431,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":293},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b59bc36-4d9a-4087-87ff-725aff05648e","uuid":"2bd6d01d-26d3-4176-bf31-ccdb536c04df"}
